<item>
            <title>[LUDOC-37] change /etc/modprobe.conf references to /etc/modprobe.d/lustre.conf</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-37</link>
                <project id="10070" key="LUDOC">Lustre Documentation</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Update the /etc/modprobe.conf references in the manual to use /etc/modprobe.d/lustre.conf.  The use of /etc/modprobe.conf has been deprecated for a long time already, and while many current distributions can use arbitrarily-named module parameter files, like in /etc/modprobe.d/Lustre, newer modutils need filenames to end in &quot;.conf&quot;, like /etc/modprobe.d/lustre.conf.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
